@startuml
title Viaverse Infrastructure / Deployment — AWS Topology Diagram

node "Users\nMobile / Web / Admin" as Users
cloud "Route 53\nDNS" as R53
cloud "CloudFront\nCDN + TLS edge" as CF
cloud "AWS WAF\nrate rules / bot guard" as WAF
node "ALB / Ingress\npublic entry" as ALB

rectangle "AWS VPC — Multi-AZ" {
  rectangle "Public Subnets" {
    node "NAT Gateways\nper AZ" as NAT
  }
  rectangle "Private App Subnets" {
    node "EKS Cluster\nSpring Boot microservices\nKMP Web BFF / Admin BFF" as EKS
    node "Service Discovery / Ingress\ninternal service routing" as Mesh
    node "Workers\nmedia / outbox / scheduler" as Workers
    node "OTel Collector\nsidecars/daemonset" as OTel
  }
  rectangle "Private Data Subnets" {
    database "RDS PostgreSQL\nMulti-AZ" as RDS
    database "ElastiCache Redis\nsessions/cache/rate" as Redis
    queue "MSK Kafka\nor managed Kafka" as Kafka
    database "S3 Buckets\nmedia/backups/log archive" as S3
    database "OpenSearch\nsearch + logs" as OpenSearch
  }
  node "KMS + Secrets Manager\nExternal Secrets sync" as KMS
  node "Prometheus / Perses / Jaeger\nobservability" as Obs
}

node "GitHub Actions\nCI/CD + IaC" as CI
node "ECR\ncontainer registry" as ECR

Users --> R53
R53 --> CF
CF --> WAF
WAF --> ALB
ALB --> EKS : HTTPS
EKS --> Mesh : internal
Mesh --> Workers : events/jobs
EKS --> OTel : telemetry
EKS --> RDS : SQL
EKS --> Redis : cache
EKS --> Kafka : events
Workers --> S3 : media/jobs
Workers --> OpenSearch : index/logs
KMS ..> EKS : secrets
CI --> ECR : push images
ECR ..> EKS : deploy image
OTel --> Obs : export

note bottom
Start managed and boring: AWS edge + EKS + RDS + Redis + Kafka + S3 + OpenSearch.
Keep all replaceable through ports/adapters, but do not run duplicate broker stacks.
end note
@enduml
